docs.abstract: Videos and photos posted on social media of a number of parties show few guests abiding by social-distancing guidelines.
docs.snippet: Videos and photos posted on social media of a number of parties show few guests abiding by social-distancing guidelines.
docs.lead_paragraph: On a humid Saturday night, under a segment of the Kosciuszko Bridge, which connects Brooklyn and Queens, hundreds of people at an illicit gathering danced and swayed to the thumps of hip-hop and electronic music. Some wore masks. Many did not.

headline.main: Rave Under the Kosciuszko Bridge: Are Illicit Parties Endangering N.Y.C.?
headline.print_headline: Are Illicit Parties Putting New Yorkers at Risk?

docs.abstract: The designer Osman Yousefzada reflects on change in the industry, straddling cultures and why he looked beyond fashion to find his voice.
docs.snippet: The designer Osman Yousefzada reflects on change in the industry, straddling cultures and why he looked beyond fashion to find his voice.
docs.lead_paragraph: “I’ve always considered myself an outsider,” Osman Yousefzada said last week, sitting on a park bench near his home in North London. “Often, I’ve also been made to feel like an outsider, working in and around institutions and industries like fashion that are rooted in white codes and elitism.”

docs.abstract: Women in the military say the horrific killing of Army Specialist Vanessa Guillen has swept the nation, galvanizing even civilians to the cause.
docs.snippet: Women in the military say the horrific killing of Army Specialist Vanessa Guillen has swept the nation, galvanizing even civilians to the cause.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the #MeToo movement gained ground, propelled by stories of women in Hollywood, the news media, restaurants and other industries, women in the military have remained in the shadows.

headline.main: A #MeToo Moment Emerges for Military Women After Soldier’s Killing
headline.print_headline: #MeToo Moment for Military Women After Soldier’s Killing

docs.abstract: The league had largely avoided fan furor over this season, but disputed calls in Sunday’s two thrilling conference championship games brought it right back.
docs.snippet: The league had largely avoided fan furor over this season, but disputed calls in Sunday’s two thrilling conference championship games brought it right back.
docs.lead_paragraph: KANSAS CITY, Mo. — The N.F.L. this season finally appeared to have accomplished its goal of “getting back to football” after several years of off-field turmoil that ranged from player misconduct to weekly protests during the national anthem. But the league’s bounce-back season was knocked off stride on Sunday, as officials in the two conference championship games made baffling, controversial calls that to some degree overshadowed the otherwise thrilling matchups.

headline.main: The N.F.L. Confronts More Controversy, This Time on the Field
headline.print_headline: The Squads Creating  The Loudest Buzz?  They Wear Stripes
